li>Send unsolicited mail or e-mail, making unsolicited phone calls or sending unsolicited faxes and/or advertise any products or services by directly posting within the Services or by making unsolicited contact with any user via email, telephone, postal mail, or any other method of communication.</li>\n 	<li>Make any changes, additions and/or deletions to any information posted by any user without the express written authorization of such other user.</li>\n 	<li>Take any action that imposes an unreasonable or disproportionately large burden on Site’s infrastructure.</li>\n 	<li>Include any hyperlinks or any misleading, irrelevant and/or hidden keywords in any information posted by you.</li>\n 	<li>Frame or link to the Site of any of the content or information available from the Site unless FinTechWP expressly consents to such linking and/or framing.</li>\n 	<li>Intentionally expose the Site and/or Service to any computer virus or any other program or code intended to disrupt or disable to operations of the Site and/or Service;</li>\n 	<li>Use any robot, spider or other program or device to retrieve or index any portion of the FinTechWP Site;</li>\n 	<li>Harvest or otherwise collect information about other users for any purpose other than use of the Site and/or Services as expressly permitted herein.</li>\n</ul>\nWith respect to FinTechWP, you acknowledge and agree to abide by the following rules, without limitation:\n<ul>\n 	<li>You must be age 16 or older to post or submit any information on the FinTechWP Site.</li>\n 	<li>Reporters, researchers and third party representatives must receive permission from FinTechWP before posting any information on the Site and/ or third party Sites.</li>\n 	<li>You may not post personally identifiable information (including without limitation, name, address, email address, phone number) about another member or any other individual without their express prior written consent.</li>\n 	<li>You agree not to impersonate any FinTechWP staff member. You also agree not to impersonate any other FinTechWP member.</li>\n 	<li>You may not post email content from private parties.</li>\n 	<li>You agree that FinTechWP reserves the right to remove any content, for any reason in its sole discretion as it may deem appropriate.</li>\n</ul>\nThe foregoing list of prohibitions is illustrative and is not intended to be complete or exclusive. FinTechWP reserves the right to terminate our relationship with you under these Terms and prohibit your access to the Site and/or Services or to edit, remove or close any posting by you for any reason, including, without limitation, any action that FinTechWP, in its sole judgment, determines to be inappropriate or disruptive to the Site, Services or to any user. If FinTechWP finds that you are abusing the private message and/or email system of FinTechWP, company may, without limitation of other available remedies, suspend or terminate your account.\n\nFinTechWP reserves the right to remove job listing if it involves adult content, an illegitimate work opportunity, an incorrect job type (i.e. freelance when it should be listed as full-time) or contains inappropriate language. After evaluation of respective case, depending on the type of breach, FinTechWP reserves the right not to issue a refund.\n\nYou acknowledge that the Site contains content that FinTechWP creates as well as content provided by third parties. The foregoing prohibitions do not impose on FinTechWP, and FinTechWP does not assume, any obligation to monitor or remove any postings or other information or communication submitted by you or any other user. You hereby acknowledge and agree that you may be exposed to content that may be offensive, indecent or objectionable or that is inaccurate, and you bear all risks associated with using that content. Your access to the Site and Services is undertaken at you own risk and FinTechWP is not responsible for any offensive or otherwise objectionable materials that may be posted by any third party. FinTechWP has the right, but not the obligation, to remove any content that may, in our sole discretion, violate these Terms or that is otherwise objectionable.\n<h4><strong>Account Registration and Password Protection</strong></h4>\nPrior to gaining access to certain Services on the Site, FinTechWP will require you to set up a user name and password (the “Password(s)”) as set forth in the account registration procedures posted on the Site. You agree to comply with the procedures specified by FinTechWP from time to time regarding obtaining and updating Passwords for the Site and Services. You agree to assume sole responsibility for the security of Passwords issued to you. Passwords are subject to cancellation or suspension by FinTechWP at any time, including upon the misuse of any and the reissuance or reactivation of Passwords. You agree to ensure that you will use your best efforts to prevent any third party from obtaining your Password, and you shall inform FinTechWP immediately in writing of any actual or potential unauthorized access to a Password or to the Site and/or Services.\n<h4><strong>Third Party Content</strong></h4>\nThird parties may provide certain information and content to FinTechWP (“Third Party Content”). The Third Party Content is, in each case, the copyrighted work of the creator/licensor, and may be subject to terms of use and/or privacy policies of such third parties. Please contact the appropriate third party for further information regarding such terms. FinTechWP disclaims all warranties and conditions with regard to content provided by third parties, including all implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and non-infringement.\n<h4><strong>Links To Third Party Sites</strong></h4>\nThis Site may provide links to other Web sites or resources over which FinTechWP does not have control (“External Web Sites”). Such links do not constitute an endorsement by FinTechWP of those External Web 